From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James M <f0rm4tm3@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 14:58:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH v3 1/2] kernelbase/tests: Add tests for CharPrevA NULL start.

Native Windows does not return NULL for the tested NULL-start cases.
It returns the previous character pointer. Add tests for CharPrevA()
and CharPrevExA() with a NULL start pointer and an in-bounds current
pointer, wrapping those calls so current Wine reports a clean failure
instead of crashing the whole test process.
---
 dlls/kernelbase/tests/Makefile.in |  3 +-
 dlls/kernelbase/tests/string.c    | 95 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 97 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 dlls/kernelbase/tests/string.c

diff --git a/dlls/kernelbase/tests/Makefile.in b/dlls/kernelbase/tests/Makefile.in
index 5362d96..df1dda1 100644
--- a/dlls/kernelbase/tests/Makefile.in
+++ b/dlls/kernelbase/tests/Makefile.in
@@ -7,4 +7,5 @@ SOURCES = \
 	process.c \
 	rsrc.rc \
 	security.c \
-	sync.c
+	sync.c \
+	string.c
diff --git a/dlls/kernelbase/tests/string.c b/dlls/kernelbase/tests/string.c
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1111111
--- /dev/null
+++ b/dlls/kernelbase/tests/string.c
@@ -0,0 +1,95 @@
